reference.title: TRCCONFIGR, Trace Configuration Register
reference.shortdesc: The TRCCONFIGR controls the tracing options.

section.title: Bit field descriptions

dd.p: Enables data value tracing. The possible values are:
Enables data address tracing. The possible values are:
Configures the Virtual context identifier value used by the trace unit, both for trace generation and in the Virtual context identifier comparators. The possible values are:

dlentry.dd: VTTBR_EL2.VMID is used. If the trace unit supports a Virtual context identifier larger than the VTTBR_EL2.VMID, the upper unused bits are always zero. If the trace unit supports a Virtual context identifier larger than 8 bits and if the VTCR_EL2.VS bit forces use of an 8-bit Virtual context identifier, bits [15:8] of the trace unit Virtual context identifier are always zero.
CONTEXTIDR_EL2 is used. TRCIDR2.VMIDOPT indicates whether this field is implemented.

dd.p: Enables Q element. The possible values are:

dlentry.dd: Q elements with instruction counts are disabled. Q elements without instruction counts are disabled.
Q elements with and without instruction counts are enabled.

dd.p: Enables the return stack. The possible values are:
Enables global timestamp tracing. The possible values are:
Enables conditional instruction tracing. The possible values are:

dlentry.dd: Conditional load and store instructions are traced.

dd.p: Enables VMID tracing. The possible values are:
Enables context ID tracing. The possible values are:
Enables cycle counting instruction trace. The possible values are:
Enables branch broadcast mode. The possible values are:
Controls whether load and store instructions are traced as P0 instructions. The possible values are:

dlentry.dd: Load and store instructions are not traced as P0 instructions.
Load instructions are traced as P0 instructions.
Store instructions are traced as P0 instructions.
Load and store instructions are traced as P0 instructions.

section.p: Bit fields and details not provided in this description are architecturally defined. See the Arm Architecture Reference Manual Armv8, for Armv8-A architecture profile.
The TRCCONFIGR can be accessed through the external debug interface, offset 010.
